. An IoT Gateway is a device that acts as a bridge between IoT sensor nodes and the cloud. It collects data from sensors, processes or filters it if required, converts different communication protocols, and securely sends the data to the cloud. It also receives commands from the cloud and forwards them to IoT devices.
Simple Diagram
+-------------+     +-------------+     +-------------+     +----------------+
| IoT Sensors | --> | IoT Gateway | --> | Cloud Server| --> | User App/Web   |
+-------------+     +-------------+     +-------------+     +----------------+
Protocols Used at Each Layer
Layer	Common Protocols
IoT Sensor Nodes → Gateway	Zigbee, LoRa, BLE, Wi-Fi
Gateway → Cloud	MQTT, HTTP, HTTPS
Cloud → User Application	HTTPS, REST API, WebSocket
